The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 July is 52,253 (6,047.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 July, there were 3,200 new confirmed cases (370.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 July, there were 2,163 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 48% (1,037 extra cases).
